Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 489
An Act to Provide for a Vessel Breakdown License Exception for
Commercial Halibut Fishing License Holders
(EMERGENCY)
Received by the Clerk of the House on February 6, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Marine Resources pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed pursuant to Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative STROUT of Harrington.
Cosponsored by Senator MOORE of Washington and
Representatives: DRINKWATER of Milford, LYMAN of Livermore Falls, QUINT of
Hodgdon, TUELL of East Machias, Senator: RENY of Lincoln.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Emergency preamble. Whereas, acts and resolves of the Legislature do not
2 become effective until 90 days after adjournment unless enacted as emergencies; and
3 Whereas, this legislation must take effect before May 18, 2025, the beginning of the
4 the 2025 commercial halibut fishing season; and
5 Whereas, in the judgment of the Legislature, these facts create an emergency within
6 the meaning of the Constitution of Maine and require the following legislation as
7 immediately necessary for the preservation of the public peace, health and safety; now,
8 therefore,
9 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
10 Sec. 1. 12 MRSA §6506, sub-§2, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 627, §5, is amended to
11 read:
12 2. Licensed activity; commercial license. The holder of a commercial halibut fishing
13 license issued under subsection 1 may fish for, take, possess, ship, transport or sell halibut
14 that the holder has taken using the vessel named on the license. Crew members aboard a
15 license holder’s vessel may fish for, take, possess, ship or transport halibut only if the
16 license provides for crew members.
17 Sec. 2. 12 MRSA §6506, sub-§2-A is enacted to read:
18 2-A. Exception to using vessel named on license holder's license for commercial
19 license holders. Notwithstanding subsection 2, the commissioner may temporarily
20 authorize a holder of a commercial halibut fishing license to use a vessel other than the
21 vessel named on that license holder's license to fish for, take, possess, ship or transport
22 halibut if the license holder documents to the commissioner that the vessel named on that
23 license holder's license has become temporarily inoperable because of an accident or a
24 mechanical failure and requests in writing to the commissioner that the commissioner
25 authorize the use of another vessel to fish for or take halibut. The commissioner's
26 authorization may require the license holder to fish for, take, possess and land halibut
27 separately from any halibut taken under another license listing the same vessel to ensure
28 that harvest limits are not exceeded. An authorization granted by the commissioner to a
29 license holder due to an accident or a mechanical failure may not exceed 2 weeks. The
30 commissioner may authorize one 2-week extension per license holder during the
31 commercial halibut fishing season.
32 Emergency clause. In view of the emergency cited in the preamble, this legislation
33 takes effect when approved.
34 SUMMARY
3355 This bill provides that the holder of a commercial halibut fishing license may fish for,
3366 take, possess, ship, transport or sell halibut that the holder has taken using only the vessel
3377 named on the license. The bill also provides an exception to this provision. It allows a
3388 commercial halibut fishing license holder to request authorization from the Commissioner
3399 of Marine Resources to use a vessel other than the vessel identified on that license holder's
4400 license when that license holder's vessel is temporarily inoperable.
