132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 489
H.P. 318 House of Representatives, February 11, 2025
An Act to Provide for a Vessel Breakdown License Exception for
Commercial Halibut Fishing License Holders
(EMERGENCY)
Received by the Clerk of the House on February 6, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Marine Resources pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed pursuant to Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative STROUT of Harrington.
Cosponsored by Senator MOORE of Washington and
Representatives: DRINKWATER of Milford, LYMAN of Livermore Falls, QUINT of
Hodgdon, TUELL of East Machias, Senator: RENY of Lincoln.
Printed on recycled paper

